        %p
          %strong Counting Money
        %p If you don't know how to count money, you won't know how much cash you have. You also might have trouble managing and budgeting your money if you can't count it to keep track of it. Coins to learn include pennies, nickels, dimes, and quarters. Pennies have a value of 1 cent, and nickels are worth 5 cents. Dimes are worth 10 cents, and quarters are worth 25 cents. Counting money is a math skill that involves figuring out the total value of coins and paper bills.
